import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='year')
    plt.plot(data['year'], data['people'])
    plt.title('What is the trend of population over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['age'].plot(kind='hist', bins=19, alpha=0.5, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['age'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['age'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['age'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['age'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of age in the population?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['sex'] = data['sex'].replace({1: 'Male', 2: 'Female'})
    sex_count = data['sex'].value_counts()
    sex_count.plot(kind='bar', color=['blue', 'pink'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of sex in the population?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    plt.scatter(data['age'], data['people'])
    plt.title('What is the relationship between age and population?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['age_group'] = data['age_group'].astype(str)
    age_group_data = data.groupby('age_group')['people'].sum().reset_index()
    age_group_data = age_group_data.sort_values(by='people', ascending=False)
    plt.bar(age_group_data['age_group'], age_group_data['people'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of population across different age groups?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Age Group')
    plt.ylabel('Population')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
